main event: A military jet and the moon were initially mistaken for an unidentified flying object near Dayton, Ohio on January 6, 1961.
interesting points: The object was initially reported as a white point in the sky that appeared to go out and move very fast.
The sighting lasted for about 10 seconds.
The witness reported the object as being the size of a quarter.
The object was determined to be a military jet and the moon after further analysis.
The witness was considered to have good reliability.
sighted object: a white point in the sky
